    "Experimental results showed that the system's gesture recognition accuracy was around 90%.",
    "It could complete barrier-free communication with deaf-mute people, the production cost was low, and the model was easy to transplant, which was suitable for popularization.",
    "Xie et al. [7] proposed a new model architecture, PiSLTRc, which was a position-informed sign language transformer with content-aware convolutions.",
    "Compared with the ordinary Transformer model, the model achieved superior performance on three large-scale sign language benchmarks.",
    "Jiang et al. [8] proposed an end-to-end continuous sign language recognition method based on Transformer, which achieved an accuracy of 96.30% on the CSL data set."
